		     	 Cross-database queries in Azure SQL Database 
 

			         
 Posted on   March 2, 2016   by   James Serra 
         

			 
			     A limitation with  Azure SQL database  has been its inability to do cross-database SQL queries.  This has changed with the introduction of  elastic database queries , now in preview.  However, it’s not as easy as on-prem SQL Server, where you can just use the three-part name syntax DatabaseName.SchemaName.TableName.  Instead, you have to define remote tables (tables outside your current database), which is similar to how  PolyBase  works for th